caption: Truthfully the best lasagna I’ve ever had, definitely the best in Brooklyn. Eat in one of their outdoor private booths or dine in, you’ll be pleased either way.
Love love love. The oxtail burger was delicious. Cocktails were good.
Lovely restaurant with delicious food and attentive service! Felt totally safe and taken care of.

The outside patio is set up very nicely, even on cold days I’ve been pretty warm. The first time I came I had the oxtail ravioli, it was very good. Last night I had the cacio e pepe and my friend had the bolognese, both were just ok. The cocktail I had was great the biggest problem was after dinner while I still had half my cocktail left the waiter gave us the check and told us he had a reservation for the table and that we had to leave. This wasn’t communicated to us before we sat down. We had to be rushed out after 45 mins of sitting down, I couldn’t even finish my cocktail. It’s just very bad customer service.

I’m always interested in trying amazing restaurants in my neighborhood.  I’ve been wanting to try this place for a while but I’m still a bit apprehensive about dining indoors.  I ordered from Grubhub & my meal came very well packed; well cooked and tasty. I had the Rib Eye which came with baby potatoes tasty gravy; the Orecchiette and Steak were done to perfection.  My meal also came with soft pieces of bread and a nice olive basil dressing.  Thanks guys

Great service, good food and the prices are reasonable for a good date night out but sadly we went on a night it was so cold that it was hard to properly enjoy our food. Nonetheless, planning to go back in the not too distant future.
Been coming here for years now for that oxtail burger. Always tasty. However, the new wave of staff has slowly become more "posh" rather than "cool." Hope to see Aita reclaim its laid back vibe!

Probably my favourite brunch in Brooklyn right now. Very well set up for covid winter with great heat lamps and plexi glass so you're in individual booths - but with the side open so you have the all important air flow.  The standard breakfast is delicious. Can't wait to come back for dinner.
Delicious food and the winter setup keeps folks warm enough (as much as could be during COVID). I cannot emphasize enough - get the aperitivo snack!
Amazing food and service. Every time.

Came for Saturday brunch the day after Christmas and both the service and food were stellar as always. The outdoor dining setup was quite clever with individual heat lamps above each booth keeping us warm even in the 30s.

Perfect outdoor seating arrangement following COVID protocols to a T! open air but enclosed on 3 sides, heat lamps above, screens between each booth, QR code for menus. And the food is and always has been incredible :)

Aita has been a neighborhood favorite for as long as I can remember—wonderful Italian food for dinner (the oxtail ravioli is a must) and a really solid brunch menu.  We stopped here on a cold day (low 30s) for brunch for outdoor seating, and it was the most comfortable outdoor dining experience we’ve had this winter—the tables were each heated with its own heater and you were separated from your neighbor with plexiglass.  The food was excellent as always and the service was friendly and attentive— their brunch menu is a combination of Italian staples and traditional brunch food. We had the spaghetti carbonara and burger, which were both delicious. Their cocktails are also inventive and tasty—we had the Kicking Sicilian hot cocktail. Would highly recommend!
Nice outdoor winter seating!
Great place to catch up with friends!

Great spot for brunch and I am sure also dinner. I reserved a table under their Gazebo (built wooden terrace with individual heater by table). My husband and I had the spaghetti carbonara for brunch; delicious and our friends the omelet and burger which also seem very appetizing. Will definitely come back for dinner.

Love Aita and the friendly staff. I've only gone for appetizers and drinks (pre-COVID) and Mayflower next door used to be my go-to bar. You can tell they really care about the quality and selection of their ingredients, wines, liquors, etc. and their martini olives are my fav in the city!
Great service for outdoor dining, one of the best dinner experiences I’ve had in Brooklyn. Fresh ingredients, never disappoints
Escape Manhattan and hop into Italy. Innovative twists on the classic. Charming setting, candles, plants... Ox stiffed ravioli with a bottle of tinto.
very good service
Great service and food!
Spaghetti was Delicious!!!

July 25, 2020: Had a fantastic social-distanced dinner here! The tables were plenty far apart (it felt like a private dinner beside the string lights) and the food was delicious as usual. It was also great that the tables were on the sidewalk, instead out out in the street like at other places across the city. Highly recommend if you’re looking for a meal out and want to stay as safe as possible.  February 11, 2020: LOVE it here!! The food is always fantastic — they even made an eggplant dish that I liked! More recently, I had fried artichokes with burrata, Brussels sprouts, and saffron gnocchi. We were also surprised with complementary butternut squash and bread to start off the meal which was super tasty. They rotate the menu pretty regularly, too, but seem to have some usual things that always make the cut.
Authentic Italian - with very relaxed atmosphere

It’s a treat having Aita as our local. The food is wonderful, the setting too. During COVID, they’ve turned into our local alcohol store too, as their unique selection of vermouth is arguably the best in the city (love when places find a niche and then excel). I appreciate them.

We stumbled upon this place by accident and had an amazing dinner! Service was nice and fast, food was absolutely delicious and drinks were great too. I found it’s hard to find a good old fashioned at a restaurant, but this one was really good. We are definitely coming back!
Had a fantastic experience in here with my girlfriend. The food arrived quickly and the customer service is just awesome. Prices are fair.
Mediocre pasta for $20

This is the kind of place you kind of don’t want to tell people about because you want to keep it for yourself. But I love this place and want to suppoort them, so here it goes: amazing pasta and gnocchi dishes, always come out steaming hot, the oxtail ravioli is my favorite and the lasagna is addictive. For the mains I usually get any of their fish dishes and they never fail with their brick chicken. They have a lovely olive oil cake which we often get for dessert. The one thing I wish is that they served their red wines at a lower temperature but honestly don’t really care as the food is so consistently good. Their take-out always comes hot and delicious too! Love!
This place is my favorite restaurant in Clinton Hill. The oxtail ravioli and oxtail burger are amazing!
Amazing
To long to remember

Aita is amazing both for brunch service as well as their dinner. Since it's amazing and super popular getting a reservation is important but since I live nextdoor and it's not much trouble to just show up I'll say Ive had consistent "luck" getting a table for 2 or room at the counter. Service is always friendly and fast. Off the dinner menu the seafood stew is maybe my favorite dish in Brooklyn, wish I could eat it everyday
Beautiful ambience. Homemade pasta. Friendliest staff. Delicious food.
Excellent atmosphere, great food, excellent service.
Incredible food and ambiance
Great food, service, and atmosphere. The seafood pasta special (squid ink spaghetti and loads of seafood) was amazing.
The food is outstanding. The gnocchi was perfectly prepared! Short wait for a table on a Saturday night.
amazing, great food, wonderful staff and service
Lovely relaxed atmosphere but our table wasn't close to ready for our reservation and it's overpriced for the quality of the food. But it doesn't seem like a crowd that's looking for "value" 😏.
Top notch
The pasta was very authentic and great. and other foods were great as well. The owner and staff were very kind and warm.

Mixed impressions but wouldn't go back - oxtail ravioli was great, servers were very nice / endearing, and atmosphere is charming. The rest of the food though was ho-hum and pretty expensive compared to what else is available in Brooklyn and they serve your food in record speed, almost like they're getting you in and out. Went for dinner - seems like people loved it though for brunch.
Best food and service in Clinton Hill
The food was absolutely delicious! Best dinner to end my trip to NY. HIGHLY RECOMMEND!!
Great food and friendly, professional staff.
Outstanding meal and ambiance

Not great. Our wedding anniversary, so we were looking for a quiet evening.  The place was totally empty when we arrived, & we were seated promptly.  10 mins later a father & 2 kids arrived and were seated directly next to us, although every other table on the place was empty. We found ourselves having to shout to each other to be heard over the kids at the next table. The menu sounded great - but was deceiving. Nothing was really what we expected. And the wine we ordered turned out to be nearly $20 more than we had thought. So not the most successful evening.
Everything we had was so delicious and peefect. I could eat their fresh pastas all day
Food was delicious.  I had the oxtail ravioli. It was as good as the review said. The whole atmosphere was welcoming. Highly recommend.
Got my order within minutes and it was freshly made, hot, tasty and spicy too. I enjoyed my food and time here, absolutely amazing place. Decent pricing on everything and truly lovely staff.
We underappreciate this place because we live just down the street, but our last meal there was excellent.
Very good food and very friendly staff
Great staff  food was very good

I tried the buttermilk pancakes with a side of pastrami salmon. The pancakes were good, but the salmon was something else. I loved the slightly cured flavor. I also ordered oxtail burger, which was perfectly prepared rare at my request; the burger has an extra umami flavor and is slightly spicy, reminding of Chinese cuisine. The service was extra attentive and very friendly. The black coffee was ok, the cold brew was served with way too much ice (and no warning).  Everything on the menu looks exciting. I can't wait to go back to try the full dinner menu.

Omg this place is literally so amazing! The closest thing you’ll get to real real Italian food in NYC! Absolutely hands down some of the best fine dining I’ve had in NY! I try to go there as much as I can- there food is just brilliant, so decadent and light and buttery! Flavors abound !! After spending 2 weeks in Florence, Italy I can attest to the authenticity of flavor Aita produces
👍 great
Warning to anyone making a reservation - Aita forces you to use Resy and charges a no show fee of $15 per head. This is not disclosed on their Resy page. Pretty lame

My girlfriend and I ate brunch here. The staff is very courteous and the chefs know what they are doing. I mean really know what they are doing. I got the meal with the poached eggs, pancakes, home fries, and greens. I think this was one of the best brunches that I've had in my life and I've been to a fair amount of establishments in Brooklyn. I definitely dream about their brunch.

so delicious! salads were refreshing and creative, pastas were delicious. oxtail ravioli was great. the waiters were very attentive and nice. the atmosphere and interior decorating was also very pleasant! this sounds weird, but definitely go to the bathroom- the decor was beautiful.

Cute small place. The pastas and cocktails were decent but the appetizer and dessert weren't very good. Overall, I wouldn't go back here. Service was fine. Although we were here on the early side and the restaurant wasn't busy, we had another couple seated right next to a very close table, which ruined the atmosphere somewhat.
The food is delicious. The service was excellent.
I ordered the omelette and it was excellent. I would also recommend the oxtail burger. Just a really great little spot.

Had a great meal, but waitress gave us our check before we finished eating and before we asked for it. Place was not even full.  Do good restaurants do this? It seemed like it ruined a great experience.

Always wonderfully fresh, seasonal food with fun staff in a beautiful location. The vegetarian options are so good and we’ve never been let down. Highly recommend for dinner and really nice for brunch.

Had a really lovey meal here (loved the pumpkin tagliatelle!) and we enjoyed the atmosphere, but unfortunately the experience was soured when we were asked to leave because a party was here for their reservation. It felt really inappropriate to kick us out, seeing that we’d just spent so much money on a meal and we were all enjoying each other company so much. The food wasn’t so good that it makes up for this kind of treatment.
Great food, great service. Great atmosphere.
Came here for brunch and the ambience was lovely and the food was delicious. Recommend getting their berry pancake on the side, so yummy.
Like it

Exceptional food, but service is unacceptably mismanaged for the price of a plate. we waited 30 min to be seated with a reservation, drinks took 45 min, food took over an hour & half to arrive and all for only $300 for two. Dude bros in sweat stained shirts stood at the bar doing shots with the manager & fist pounding each other rather than serving. Ran out of the main course of a four course dinner and still charged us full amount plus drinks. Many customers around us left before they were served anything due to the wait. Very poorly managed restaurant, will not be back.

Terrible service.

Arrived at 6:30 and were seated without a reservation.  We had finished our meal, after having our dishes removed quite promptly after each course, and on two occasions an attempt was made to remove our plates before we were finished. At  8:00 pm, we had just finished our dessert, were presented with the check, and then 10 minutes later, we were requested to move to the bar, because they had a reservation for which they needed our table. It was the height of rudeness. I spoke with the manager, (or at least The woman who had requested we give up out table) and suggested that if they had a deadline for the table they should have let us know when we sat down.  Her response wAs “well ok” and then she added two hours is customary to allow for dinner.  I pointed out that we had arrived at 6:30, and she said “well that’s about two hours.....” Such treatment was inexcusable and left a very bad taste in my mouth.
Great brunch selection for less of a wait then the more known high traffic brunch places. Great coffee too!
Great service. .. deeeelicious food. Hispter (authentic) Italian 👌🏽

This place has a ton going for it. Super cute, great location, staff were very friendly, and prices were reasonable. Nice drinks menu, and it's right next door to one of my favorite bars, The Mayflower. I really wanted to love it, but the pasta dishes we ordered were surprisingly flat and uninspired. We'll probably give it another try sometime, but will steer clear of the pasta portion of the menu (particularly the spaghetti dish w/pesto. Very wet, unsalted, with no discernible pesto...) All in all, the restaurant as a whole was fantastic, but the food didn't measure up.
Upscale pizza with an attentive and friendly staff.
Good neighborhood Italian restaurant whose lunches and brunches are puzzlingly better than their dinners.
Fantastic Italian food made with great care in a charming location. What more could you want?
Good food, good service.
Great food and surprisingly good wine list. Service was amazing.

This is a small neighborhood spot that always has fantastic food. It is very difficult to get a table here and it's a bit on the pricey side so just be aware of that. Best to go early in the evening if you can.
Old folks home must be nice to the seniors.
Delicious brunch

Aita is deninetely one of my favorite Italian restaurant in Brooklyn and NY .As Italian  when i go to Italian restaurants what i want is quality and authenticity, and every time i step into Aita i always feel very welcome. I have to say the fettuccine and buttata are beyond !

Beautiful romantic restaurant. The food was to die for and the service is very good. Def a place to have a romantic date and the drinks were very good. Will definitely recommend if you are in the area. Steak was huge and they make their own pasta. Very fresh

Had a fantastic meal here! We came in around 830 pm with no reservation on a Monday night. Quickly got a seat at the bar. Absolutely loved the burrata with fresh melons. So delicious on a hot day. Pasta was amazing as well. Definitely recommend coming here for a quiet evening meal.

Delicious.The brunch was amazing. I recommend the avocado poached eggs. Service was also great.

Consistently good.

Simply delicious! Just go and eat.
Small cozy, has a nice home feel to it, food is awesome and has great service.

This place has been batting a thousand today! Other than waiting a little too long for my last small plate, everything was perfect! We got the Groupon for 4 small plates and two bottomless drinks (check it out if it's still available), and the wall is littered with deals and steals like happy hours, dinner specials, and great prices on their regular drink ($5-9) and food menus ($7 per small plate, $19 for 3)! The service was frequent, friendly, and relaxed! Who are these people!? I had the lobster roll (seasonal special fresh that day from Maine, the Brioche French Toast topped with fruit, and chose the Bloody Mary. The lobster was on baked "steamed bun" generously drizzled in a savory, saucy slaw that complimented the amazingly fresh lobster (I could taste the fresh ocean). The Brioche French Toast is lighted toasted on top, crispy on the side and moist in the center, and rivals Square One's French toast! The blood Mary was on point, very flavor with equal parts salty, smoky, spicy, and strong!!! The same was true of my girlfriends screw driver, a strong drink with sharp citrus flavors that went to down smooth! Even my vegan girlfriend's tofu scramble made me believe I was actually eating eggs! This is definitely going to be a regular brunch and dine spot.
Good food here
Delicious 😋
Amazing food, drinks and energy! Super recommended.

This place was amazing. Small and cozy with great music! Everyone who worked there was very helpful and accommodating. We got our food quick and it was amazing. My husband had the linguine with clams, my brother-in-law had the oxtail ravioli. I have quite a few food allergies and they would more than happy to help me choose an item. I had the mushroom dish and it was amazing as well.  The manager was engaging and wonderful to talk to. Check out the speakeasy next door.
Amazing atmosphere, great service, excellent authentic food, and good cocktails. Also try the cocktail bar next door!
Wonderful Eggs Benedict and delicious coffee!

This place has fantastic pasta and has become a local favorite of mine. The other dishes are quite good as well. The only thing that is kind of odd is the wine list... maybe just a little too avant-garde for my tastes.
Ate here with a friend. Well worth the long walk from where I was staying.
Fantastic brunch spot. Little hidden gem.

The mozzarella dish had grilled apples in it, and was hopin with flavor. It was busy and a little loud, they played oldie hits smooth rock like wild thing, and Elton John. I want to go back. I want to go back so bad. Someone please take me to dinner.
Had only gnocchi and some Ragu pasta but both were delicious, really good. Place is cozy and nice. I'll def go back there
OH LAAWWWDDDDD you don't even know how much respect for this place I have. Veal Ragu y'all!
Excellent fish and house made pasta.
The gnocchi melted in my mouth.  They were like little angel pillows.  Amazing!  It's quiet and quaint; great for a date spot or an intimate evening with girlfriends.

I feel unfair rating this place until I visit for a meal, but I popped in on a weekday to have a couple of (perfect) glasses of wine at the bar with a friend and I was charmed! Nice and quiet. Food was good and service was great.

Amazing amazing food, for both lunch and dinner. Favorite lunch item is by far the bison burger, with the pickled red cabbage. I got it once without it and it wasn't the same. Favorite dinner item is the suckling pig. I looked them up online and they're awfully cute, ugh i'm so torn. Anyway, it's really delicious. Everything is.
Cozy spot for weekend day drinking and nice Italian inspired brunch dishes.
Food is great. If the bread can be hot, it will be better.

I've been here a few times --I just took my parents here and they love it too. The food is simply amazing. It gets busy around lunch time even at on weekdays at 1-2 PM but it's worth it. The server is nice and very friendly. Get their oxtail burger or lasagna ❤.
